          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C (140°C fan). Line a deep 20 cm round tin with baking paper. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in {{self-raising-flour}}, then stir through {{sultanas}}, {{mixed-peel}}, {{glace-cherries}}, {{lemon}} zest, and {{whole-milk}}. Spoon into the tin and smooth the top. Scatter {{almonds-flaked}} over the surface and press them in gently. Bake for 70 to 75 minutes until a skewer comes out clean and the almonds are deep gold. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes before turning out.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
